2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Peter Hill was born about 1580, in Cornwall, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. Anne Hill about 1600, in Modbury, Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"about 1580–":"umbes 1580–Surnud","1577–Female":"1577–Surnud","1603–Male":"1603–Surnud","1604–1667":"1604–1667","1580–Male":"1580–Surnud","about 1580":"umbes 1580","1667":"1667","1577":"1577","29 MAY 1603":"29. mai 1603","Abt 1600":"umbes 1600","1580":"1580","1604":"1604","1603":"1603","Wells, Somersetshire, England":"Wells, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Modbury,Devon,England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Modbury, Devonshire, England":"Modbury, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Cornwall, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1580–":"noin 1580–Kuollut","1577–Female":"1577–Kuollut","1603–Male":"1603–Kuollut","1604–1667":"1604–1667","1580–Male":"1580–Kuollut","about 1580":"noin 1580","1667":"1667","1577":"1577","29 MAY 1603":"29. toukokuuta 1603","Abt 1600":"noin 1600","1580":"1580","1604":"1604","1603":"1603","Wells, Somersetshire, England":"Wells, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Modbury,Devon,England":"Modbury, Devon,